  "_comment": "Sprint 6 (decision 27) — stratification spec for the doc-views eval set. The generator authors ~`quota` realistic USER queries per family, each targeting a sampled criterion id in that family (by-construction label, E8). Goal: exercise the vector tail ACROSS the catalog, not in proportion to real query frequency. DRAFT v1 — judgment calls flagged below; tweak quotas/patterns freely.",
  "_judgment_calls": [
    "PERIOD IS ORTHOGONAL: there is no 'halves' family. A period-suffixed stat market ('Total Corners - 1st Half') buckets to its STAT family (corners), not a period bucket — period is a facet, not an intent.",
    "ORDERED = PRIORITY: a criterion joins the FIRST family whose subject matches and whose name contains any pattern. Specific stat families precede the generic 'result' / 'other_specials' catch-alls (so 'Corners Handicap' lands in corners, not result).",
    "MAINSTREAM-WEIGHTED: result/goals/scorers/corners/cards get bigger quotas; the huge Specials/novelty tail is down-weighted to a small 'other_specials' catch-all so it's covered but doesn't drown the signal.",
    "BLIND: within a family the generator sees only the target market (name+category+subject) — never the doc-views, never the failure list."
  ],
